People frame raw versus pasteurized milk as a tradition versus technology thing but advanced PCR type methods allow rapid testing for Brucellosis, Salmonella, and other diseases. It's like why you no longer have to overcook pork from the store like people did in the 20th century.

It made sense to pasteurize foods in the early 20th century but w/ good testing you can partially phase it out just like you can switch to intradermal vaccination rather than intramuscular when a disease is no longer common in a population. No one wants to be a moderate centrist.
